The paper focuses on the development of a tool for requirements elicitation in the Traffic Management (TM) domain, which is a software engineering problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning approaches such as Natural Language Processing and Naive Bayes, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The tool is designed for Android-based devices, which could fall under the category of cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity). The paper also mentions the involvement of stakeholders from both software development and transportation engineering, which could fall under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper mentions the interactive nature of the tool, which could fall under the category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
